{
  "texts": [
    "It then follows that iκ 2 has the behaviour lim z→z * a iκ 2 (z) ∼ ln(z -z * a).",
    "This behaviour means that, as claimed, lim z→z * a ξ + (z) = 0 as follows from the bosonization of ξ + (2.19).",
    "We can explicitly include such charged states in the path integral by inserting the non-local operators dz e iκ 2 (z), (2.23) with the contour being taken around z * a.",
    "We will comment briefly on this further in section 6.",
    "To all intents, we can think of the points z * a as additional punctures in the worldsheet where a state with one unit of κ 2 charge is inserted.Despite also carrying a background charge, we do not need to add insertions for κ 1 in order to construct correlation functions in the Wakimoto representation."
  ]
}